

# ── Subject ────────────────────────────────────|── 72 hard limit ────|
#
# ── Body: wrap at 72 ─────────────────────────────────────────────────|
#
# 50 = GitHub readability sweet spot (Desktop warns here)
# 72 = GitHub truncates subject on commit list beyond this
# 72 = body wrap matches git log's 4-space indent on 80-col terminal
#
# ── Conventional Commits types ────────────────────────────────────────
#   feat      New feature
#   fix       Bug fix
#   refactor  Code improvement (no behavior change)
#   docs      Documentation (including code comments)
#   test      Add or change tests
#   perf      Performance improvement
#   style     Formatting, lint fixes
#   chore     Maintenance, dependencies, tooling
#
# ── Rules ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   Subject:  imperative mood, no period, lowercase after type
#   Scope:    optional (e.g. feat(tmux), fix(zsh))
#   Body:     explain *why*, not *what*
#   Footer:   Breaking-Change: / Co-Authored-By: / Refs: #issue
